node.text:
2021 is a new dawn for ASICS.​ #SoundMindSoundBody #ad

The founding mission and story is more important than ever as the world faces a mental health pandemic.​ This year, they are recommitting to the ASICS founding philosophy of Sound Mind, Sound Body. Everything we do in 2021 and beyond will help people everywhere experience the positive mental benefits of sport. The mission: to move minds. They inspire individuals to move at sunrise for their own mental wellbeing and to support others.

Sunrise is one of my favorite symbols of hope. So, to kick off 2021, let’s spread some positivity.​ Join me by moving at sunrise and sharing your #SunriseMind selfie. @asicstennis

I know I am late, but it’s never too late with Wimbledon post. I wanted to write few words and acknowledge this wonderful piece of art whose author is unknown (at least to me). When I first saw this picture I was emotional. It brought me back to childhood and my first tennis steps. When I was a kid, I was constructing Wimbledon trophy out of improvised material I could find in my room. I was looking myself in the mirror, saying “I am Novak Djokovic, Wimbledon champion”. To win this sacred and most special tournament for me for 6th time is surreal. I am blessed and grateful to experience many beautiful moments on the holy grass of Wimbledon. My imagination was very realistic. As every kid, I dreamed,imagined,visualized and believed 100% in my dreams, like they were already achieved. Imagination and visualization is a super power.When children dream and imagine,it’s the purest form of love and motivation. I was fortunate that I had parents and few more other close people in my career that allowed me to dream and believe I can reach the stars in tennis. I am not saying that everyone will succeed in reaching the biggest heights in tennis. As a parent I believe creating loving and caring environment where we as parents show respect and support for children’s dreams,can do many wonders for our society and sports ecosystem as a whole 🙏❤️🙌

Знам да касним,али никада није прекасно за објаву о Вимблдону.Желео сам да се осврнем на ову прелепу слику и уметничко дело које је изазвало у мени пуно лепих осећања и подсетило ме на детињство. Када сам правио Вимблдонски трофеј од свих материјала који су ми били при руци. Тада сам се гледао у огледало и замислио да држим прави трофеј Вимблдона једнога дана. Слика у глави је била врло јасна и веровао сам у своју машту у потпуности. Имао сам среће да ме родитељи подрже,уз неколико блиских људи,и створе средину у којој сам могао да следим своје снове. Визуализација/Замишљање и Машта су Супер Моћи које имамо као људи. Не може свако да се домогне највиших спортских висина али у том невином и чистом дечјем развоју смо ми као родитељи обавезни да пружимо љубав, подршку, разумевање и нежност. Наставак у коментарима 👇
